HEADWORD: otherworldly
<hw>otherworldly</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>existing outside
of or not in accordance with nature.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nonnatural, preternatural, transcendental.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not worldly; preparing for or concerned primarily
with the afterlife; -- of people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source></p>

<p><ent>Othman</ent>⟦br⟧
